article.headline: Wagner rallies to beat Georgetown 28-21
article.story: STATEN ISLAND, N.Y. -- Dominique Williams had 162 yards rushing and scored the game-winning touchdown late in the fourth quarter to give Wagner a 28-21 win over Georgetown in the season opener for both teams Saturday. Down 21-7 at halftime, the Seahawks charged back in the second half as Williams scored off a lateral from Tyree Watkins in the third quarter. Deangelo James picked off a pass from Isaiah Kempf and returned it 24 yards for a touchdown to tie the game at 21. Williams converted a fourth down and scored a 6-yard touchdown six plays later with 2:49 on the clock. It was the 21st 100-yard game of his career. Georgetown went four and out on the ensuing drive. Kempf went 23 for 38 with 198 yards and a touchdown for the Hoyas. Wagner's Matt Misley completed 12 of 21 passes for 106 yards, two touchdowns and a pair of interceptions.
